creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2017-06-13T19:46:43</date>

abstract.value: The Ghost Dance Archive is a collection of correspondence and manuscripts sent to and/or written by the editor of <emph render="italic">Ghost Dance: The International Quarterly of Experimental Poetry</emph>, Hugh Fox. Though this little magazine would exist well beyond the 1960's, this collection reflects the early years of its existence and the writings of some of its notable contributors. The collection also includes issues 1 and 2 of <emph render="italic">Ghost Dance</emph>.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations should take the following form:<lb/><lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Ghost Dance Archive; MSS 14; box number; folder number; <address><addressline>Fales Library and Special Collections</addressline></address> , New York University Libraries.
Series IV: Manuscripts: contains eight folders of writings by Hugh Fox, Sharon Asselin, Frederico Undiano.
